Unistool

The three-legged Unistool is designed to be used in the living room, kitchen, dining room or even in an office or a studio. Its simple and carved as one-piece without any hardware. Its unique style blends with almost any interior style.

Dimensions: 410(W) x 700(H)
Material: Solid Wood
Designer: Shweta Suthar

Swoofer

We all love retro style. Dont we? This gorgeous speaker table is a excellent combination of modern and retro style furniture. Swoofer is a designer furniture that lifts the timeless character of your home and is a wonderful accessory to have by your bed or lounge. Pair it with your phone using Bluetooth and enjoy your favourite music.

Dimensions: 400(W) x 390(D) x 500(H)
Material: Solid Wood / Bent Plywood
Designer: Shweta Suthar

Capsule Figures

Capsule Figures is an army of characters comprising of Peace, Love, Hate, and Curlie adding to your collectible range. The wooden capsule figures are made of premium hardwoods and eco-friendly wood glue.

These capsule figures are free of paints, dyes, and stains.

Dimensions: 50(W) x 100(H)
Material: Wood
Designer: Shweta Suthar

Booster Back
1/1
Booster

Booster is a wooden collectible figure made from ash wood and cast iron. Booster is created by Polygon with a lot of love and passion. He is a joyful, chubby and friendly character. He can pose at your desk or a shelf and remind you of the joy and happiness around you.

He is currently busy making a family with his partner expect him with a dog and a couple of babies soon.

Material: Ash Wood & Cast Iron
Dimensions: 155(H) x 200(W) x 87(D)
Designer: Shweta Suthar

Contact us

Macleay Street N.10

The terrace-inspired townhouses of Macleay Street N.10 make creative use of space, horizontal and vertical. Our deep understanding of real-world material finishes, precise camera angle and generous sunlight helped us to best showcase the unique vertical void.

1/1
Nu

nu lamp is crafted from solid Panda marble with black and white veins. A subtle diffused glow is produced around the lower section when lit. Marble being a natural stone, the hue and veining varies from piece to piece, making each piece unique.

Dimensions: 150(W) x 300(H)
Material: Concrete and Panda Marble
Designer: Shweta Suthar

Bench Back
1/1
Bench

From designer Miheer Fyzee, this bench is a simple yet elegant artistic bespoke piece of furniture handcrafted out of teak wood with Sycamore Inlay. It has a personality of its own – constructed using no hardware at all, making it not only a truly beautiful piece of furniture, but a feat of craftsmanship and prestigious furniture you will ever own.

The design employs engineers techniques for strength and comfort in an otherwise minimal form.

Made to order.

Material: Teak with Sycamore Inlay
Dimension: 406(H) x 1524(W) x 355(D)
Weight: 16kg

Linie Rugs Back
1/1
Linie Rugs

Our range of rugs, collectively named Linie, bring together Danish design, New Zealand wool and artisan Indian weavers. The result is a tight, gentle texture under the feet that catch the eye with striking colour and design.

Polygon is proud to provide our weavers with safe employment conditions and family education programs, empowering communities with new economic opportunities.

    Bringing homes to life with photo-realistic architectural renderings, walkthroughs and interior design.

    We produce high quality visualisations for developments of all sizes, discovering and exploring perspectives of your property otherwise gone unseen.

    Shweta Suthar
    Founding Director & Principle Designer

    Shweta is a qualified industrial and interior designer with over a decade of experience. She has an eye for revealing beautiful, unique perspectives in every project with photorealism that lets you forget you’re looking at a visualisation.

    Bhavin Suthar
    Director

    Bhavin manages the business operations of UkkashaNuman. He works with architects and developers to explore how Polygon can take their projects beyond an ordinary visualisation.

    Site by AR.Ukkasha

    Bringing life to the home with homeware and furnishings, designed in-house and hand crafted across the world.

    We design and curate homewares, furnishings and products that experiment with form, material and function and are produced by artisans across the world.

    Shweta Suthar
    Founding Director & Principle Designer

    Shweta is a qualified industrial and interior designer with over a decade of experience. She holds a passion for innovating with material and form and introduces traditional crafting techniques from artisans across the world into her work.

    Bhavin Suthar
    Director

    Bhavin manages the business operations of UkkashaNuman. He fulfils a design and production network that engages artisans from across the world.

    Miheer Fyzee
    Product Designer & Craftsperson

    Miheer designs precision, handcrafted furniture pieces, having built a career on combining a mechanical engineering with his flair for artistic creativity.
